cast.text:
Disagree. 

The problem is that it positions Solana as having opinions on politics and culture war issues. Whatever they may be.

If Solana is seriously vying to be the base layer of the internet of value then it needs to be neutral and unopinionated or it will isolate itself from users.  We're not trying to reimagine politically siloed corporate social networks as politically siloed blockchains.

The internet is neutral and apolitical. No one wonders what the internet's position is on gender studies or DEI. As a consequence everyone uses it, left and right. 

Blockchain should be the same.

..AND it was super cringe.
